You can cook, too?

263
00:14:37,210 --> 00:14:39,020
I rotate with Shiori.

264
00:14:39,020 --> 00:14:40,940
Shiori, what's wrong?

265
00:14:41,990 --> 00:14:43,940
It's nothing.

266
00:14:43,940 --> 00:14:47,440
74th Okubo Osamu Shuto Kyoko 75th Yakuin Jiro Watanabe Akari Omure Yutaka

267
00:14:49,450 --> 00:14:50,950
Jiro-chan!

268
00:14:50,950 --> 00:14:54,520
Whoa, man! Think about time, place, and occasion, would you?

269
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:56,230
What's the meaning of that?

270
00:14:56,230 --> 00:14:57,270
Of what?

271
00:14:57,270 --> 00:14:59,130
The month-end evaluation!

272
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:03,430
Hey, Jiro-chan, what happened?

273
00:15:03,430 --> 00:15:06,150
If there was a reason for it, it was your fault, right?

274
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:08,660
What's it matter? Just leave it alone.

275
00:15:14,190 --> 00:15:16,390
I wonder what the right choice would've been.

276
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:21,100
At first, I thought she was just making fun of me.

277
00:15:21,780 --> 00:15:25,690
I thought that after she made me take her seriously, she'd laugh and call me stupid.

278
00:15:26,610 --> 00:15:28,570
But her hand...

279
00:15:28,570 --> 00:15:31,500
was shockingly cold and trembling.

280
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:35,870
Her nervousness and uncertainty became painfully clear to me.

281
00:15:36,430 --> 00:15:39,050
She's probably the same as me.

282
00:15:40,660 --> 00:15:43,880
It seemed like it was all new to her, too...

283
00:15:44,110 --> 00:15:46,370
Any guy would want to have se—

284
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:49,380
It's cold.

285
00:15:51,490 --> 00:15:53,270
If that's true, then...

286
00:15:55,670 --> 00:15:57,890
I'm the absolute worst.

287
00:15:57,890 --> 00:16:00,390
What's this all of a sudden?

288
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:03,260
Jiro-chan, don't you have a handkerchief?

289
00:16:03,260 --> 00:16:04,620
Oh, Shiori.

290
00:16:05,430 --> 00:16:07,150
Hey, Jiro-kun...

291
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:11,150
Do you have a little time to talk with me, just the two of us?

292
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:12,360
Sure.

293
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:13,780
Are you serious?

294
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:18,410
Wow!

295
00:16:18,650 --> 00:16:20,410
The breeze feels so nice.

296
00:16:20,950 --> 00:16:23,920
Shiori, is what you wanted to talk about...

297
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:27,670
Jiro-kun, did something happen between you and Watanabe-san?

298
00:16:30,170 --> 00:16:32,860
Yeah. You could call it a fight,

299
00:16:32,860 --> 00:16:35,210
or you could say I didn't express myself well...

300
00:16:35,210 --> 00:16:37,800
I had the wrong idea about her.

301
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:40,960
But I couldn't find the right timing to apologize.

302
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:43,980
And Watanabe doesn't seem like she wants to talk to me.

303
00:16:43,980 --> 00:16:46,300
Even though you're living together?

304
00:16:46,300 --> 00:16:47,020
Huh?

305
00:16:47,810 --> 00:16:51,570
In a day's time, you're with her more than you're with anyone else.

306
00:16:51,570 --> 00:16:55,210
I think Watanabe-san will understand you.

307
00:16:55,910 --> 00:16:59,580
I've been your friend since we were little, so I can vouch for you!

308
00:17:00,050 --> 00:17:01,880
That makes us even, right?

309
00:17:01,880 --> 00:17:03,180
Shiori...

310
00:17:03,850 --> 00:17:06,290
I really don't stand a chance against you.

311
00:17:06,930 --> 00:17:10,090
You've always beaten me when it comes to discussions.

312
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:14,030
I'm very much still your childhood friend, after all.

313
00:17:14,030 --> 00:17:15,250
Ahem!

314
00:17:17,010 --> 00:17:20,270
Still, I was impressed you'd noticed that something was wrong.

315
00:17:20,270 --> 00:17:23,600
Though, I guess anyone who saw that month-end evaluation would know.

316
00:17:29,620 --> 00:17:31,040
It makes me feel jealous.

317
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:37,110
I'm back.

318
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:41,120
600 watts 2 min. 30 sec.

319
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:57,380
Watanabe, I'd like to talk for a minute...

320
00:17:57,380 --> 00:18:00,140
But, yeah, you're not gonna come out, huh?

321
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:05,980
So come in, then.

322
00:18:10,650 --> 00:18:13,000
It smells like a girl!

323
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,150
I didn't expect her to just ignore my existence.

324
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:22,160
S-So, um, I'm sorry about before.

325
00:18:24,230 --> 00:18:26,830
It's not like you did anything wrong.

326
00:18:26,830 --> 00:18:27,660
No!

327
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:29,760
It's all my fault!

328
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:32,950
That was just me trying too hard and getting nowhere!

329
00:18:32,950 --> 00:18:34,820
Don't make me say it all out loud!

330
00:18:36,460 --> 00:18:38,420
It's fine, so just forget all of it!

331
00:18:38,420 --> 00:18:39,430
Right now!

332
00:18:40,370 --> 00:18:43,930
Look, it seems like you got the wrong idea, so I'll say this...

333
00:18:47,270 --> 00:18:50,630
It's not like I didn't want to, okay?

334
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:52,440
I am a guy, after all.

335
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:55,070
And to tell the truth, it's just like you said.

336
00:18:55,070 --> 00:18:58,190
I've had wild fantasies about you more than once.

337
00:18:58,190 --> 00:19:02,580
And, well, I'm actually really grateful to you for that experience...

338
00:19:02,580 --> 00:19:04,120
That's enough!

339
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:05,170
Are you stupid?!

340
00:19:05,170 --> 00:19:06,680
Don't say all that! Are you stupid?!

341
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:08,200
It's sexual harassment!

342
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:11,470
You're in a girl's room, and you have zero tact!

343
00:19:11,470 --> 00:19:14,660
And that's why you'll never be able to "graduate"!

344
00:19:14,660 --> 00:19:16,710
Y-You're quite right.

345
00:19:17,130 --> 00:19:19,200
But the reason I stopped you then was...

346
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:22,430
I just... I don't really know, but...

347
00:19:22,430 --> 00:19:26,220
I just felt like I had to treat you with more care than that.

348
00:19:26,820 --> 00:19:29,590
The idea of doing something like that in the heat of the moment

349
00:19:29,590 --> 00:19:31,730
just made me feel uneasy somehow.

350
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:33,980
I don't really get it, but...

351
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,600
Huh? What are you talking about?

352
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:37,730
It's the same now!

353
00:19:37,990 --> 00:19:40,700
I really hate things being this awkward between us.

354
00:19:41,290 --> 00:19:44,310
I want to be able to talk to you normally, like we did before.

355
00:19:44,310 --> 00:19:45,990
And I want to eat together.

356
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:51,250
Would you please give me a chance?

357
00:19:58,250 --> 00:20:01,510
Watanabe, I want to be...

358
00:20:06,750 --> 00:20:08,670
a married couple with you again.

359
00:20:16,900 --> 00:20:17,970
No! Not like that!

360
00:20:17,970 --> 00:20:19,960
When I said "married couple," I meant the practical!

361
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:22,600
O-O-Of course I realize that you have Tenjin!

362
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:25,780
I'm not going to get in the way of that... er...

363
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:26,780
Pff... Pff?

364
00:20:29,570 --> 00:20:30,720
Oh, man!

365
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:33,300
What? Why are you laughing?

366
00:20:33,300 --> 00:20:34,920
You're acting so desperate!

367
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:39,070
And what was all that? A proposal? That's hilarious!

368
00:20:40,550 --> 00:20:44,050
W-Well, you said we should stop being a married couple!

369
00:20:44,260 --> 00:20:46,920
Huh? But we can't stop.

370
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:49,060
It's something the school decided.

371
00:20:49,250 --> 00:20:50,300
What?!

372
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:53,040
So that was a lie, then?!

373
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:54,360
You lied?!

374
00:20:54,360 --> 00:20:55,560
Why?!

375
00:20:56,100 --> 00:20:59,070
How scary. It wasn't a lie. More of a vibe.

376
00:20:59,070 --> 00:21:02,460
Do you have any idea how much I agonized over this?

377
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:08,220
I think I'm enjoying this married life more than I thought I would.

378
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:15,330
I like you quite a lot, Jiro.

379
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:17,960
What is this?

380
00:21:18,870 --> 00:21:20,760
Why'd she suddenly use my first name?

381
00:21:20,760 --> 00:21:23,060
What does she mean by "like"?

382
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:27,120
What about you, Jiro?

383
00:21:27,880 --> 00:21:29,100
I...

384
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:37,230
A hand?

385
00:21:38,470 --> 00:21:41,480
Just kidding! Too bad for you!

386
00:21:42,390 --> 00:21:45,490
Sometimes the heat of the moment is important, Repressed-kun.

387
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,990
Watanabe...

388
00:21:48,910 --> 00:21:50,640
Welcome home, Jiro.

389
00:21:53,990 --> 00:21:55,050
Good to be back.

390
00:21:55,520 --> 00:21:57,200
We're not going back to square one.

391
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,850
We're starting from zero.

392
00:22:11,280 --> 00:22:14,060
I like you quite a lot, Jiro.

393
00:22:16,590 --> 00:22:18,140
I said it.

394
00:22:19,940 --> 00:22:23,920
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

395
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:28,350
I want to give love a try

396
00:22:28,350 --> 00:22:31,260
In this night when everything begins to overflow

397
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:33,530
I match my stride to yours

398
00:22:33,530 --> 00:22:39,370
The clock hands stop, charmed by a fleeting curse

399
00:22:39,370 --> 00:22:43,940
The answers always slip away

400
00:22:43,940 --> 00:22:47,360
All I want is to do it over again

401
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:52,760
If I did, would this unsettling gloom inside me disappear?

402
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:57,060
I want to know where my heart is hiding

403
00:22:57,060 --> 00:23:01,840
One day this will end

404
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:04,640
I know that

405
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:06,350
And I know the signs of discord

406
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:08,400
Turn them inside out

407
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:10,000
Don't let them pile up

408
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:14,210
I don't want things to stay unfinished like this

409
00:23:14,210 --> 00:23:18,250
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

410
00:23:18,250 --> 00:23:22,680
I want to give love a try

411
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:24,700
Everything begins to overflow

412
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:27,890
On this day when we don't know how much time is left to us

413
00:23:27,890 --> 00:23:36,150
I want your thoughts to drift toward me fondly, again and again

414
00:23:49,990 --> 00:23:53,740
Burned

415
00:23:51,270 --> 00:23:53,310
A burned rolled omelet.

416
00:23:54,280 --> 00:23:55,490
Akari, fretting.

417
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,120
And standing behind her...

418
00:23:58,120 --> 00:23:59,750
Jiro, holding sugar.

419
00:23:59,750 --> 00:24:00,770
So it's your fault?

420
00:23:59,750 --> 00:24:02,250
Ow, ow, ow Ow, ow, ow

421
00:24:00,770 --> 00:24:02,250
I thought it'd taste better that way!

422
00:24:02,250 --> 00:24:03,500
SHFF You'd better take responsibility for it.

423
00:24:03,500 --> 00:24:05,000
GULP GULP CHOMP

424
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:06,500
Ow! Ow! I'm sorry It's bitter...

425
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:10,010
Next Time A Hero, but Not the Main Character.

426
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:07,690
Next time...

427
00:24:07,690 --> 00:24:09,790
"A Hero, but Not the Main Character."

